The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Broads comments
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Broads comments
                      
	Melbourne: Match Referee Chris Broad has admitted that umpire Rudi Koertzen was possibly wrong in not referring a close stumping appeal against Sourav Ganguly to the third umpire during the second Test in Mohali.         
	Koertzen had ruled in favour of Sourav instead of referring the Aussie appeal to the third umpire even though TV replays later showed that Souravs foot might have been in the air when Brad Haddin dislodged the bails.         
	[International Cricket Council (ICC) chief executive Haroon Lorgat, when contacted by The Telegraph, refused to comment on Broads statement but added that the ICCs regulation of not commenting on an umpires decision also applies to the Match Referee, adds Our Correspondent in Mohali.]                                                                                                                          
